WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.009 --> 00:00:02.009
To create a learning module in Blackboard,

1
00:00:02.210 --> 00:00:05.590
click on the add content button in the center of the page.

2
00:00:06.210 --> 00:00:06.670
From there,

3
00:00:07.050 --> 00:00:10.550
a menu will appear on the left-hand side with all content options.

4
00:00:11.130 --> 00:00:12.829
Select the learning module link.

5
00:00:13.699 --> 00:00:16.000
This will create a header in the course content area

6
00:00:16.459 --> 00:00:18.959
where all materials and assignments will be assigned to.

7
00:00:19.879 --> 00:00:21.959
Name the folder as needed and click the visible

8
00:00:21.959 --> 00:00:24.299
to students in the drop-down menu below that.

9
00:00:25.149 --> 00:00:26.110
In the text box,

10
00:00:26.229 --> 00:00:27.969
add a description for the module.

11
00:00:28.430 --> 00:00:31.750
The force sequence button locks the materials in the module in place,

12
00:00:31.829 --> 00:00:34.389
so students must follow the information in sequence.

13
00:00:35.250 --> 00:00:38.610
This button is designed to keep them from skipping portions of the modules.

14
00:00:39.090 --> 00:00:40.409
Add an image if desired,

15
00:00:40.560 --> 00:00:41.529
then click save.